 Having trouble viewing the embedded video? Click here for an alternative.JOHANNESBURG - Opposition leaders held a media briefing session in Braamfontein earlier, to outline their plan for a national day of action which is scheduled for Monday, 15 May 2017.This is the day the Constitutional Court hears the application for a secret ballot in the motion of no confidence in President Jacob Zuma.IN PICTURES: Day of Action Malema calls ANC MPs cowardsThe parties behind the march include the African Christian Democratic Party (ACDP), African Independent Congress (AIC), African People's Convention (APC), Agang SA, Congress of the People (Cope), Democratic Alliance (DA), Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF), Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP) and the United Democratic Movement (UDM).The briefing was held at the Parktonian Hotel.eNCA